profile_bio:
I like coding, so I do it every day.
If I don’t do it, I feel like I've done nothing for the whole day.
I usually go to cafe to work whenever I have free time, such as on the weekends or when I'm on holiday.
Some people think that's strange or bizarre, but, don't get me wrong, I enjoy it!

I would really love to share the information with someone interested in IT.
So as a first step for it, I decided to start my own blog.
I’d be really happy if someone could get some information through the blog.
So I’m posting data on it steadily to share with others.

Sometimes, I feel like I focus too much on programming.
For some people, it seem like a waste of time.
I’ve been focusing too much on programming, so sometimes I spend a lot of time for it.
Technically, For some people, it seems like wasteful.
Even through it is slow and unnecessary practically, I’m just thinking that I’m doing right.
Through these steps, I’m steadily improving my technological skills.

Now, I’m developing more toward a front-end, because I have an aptitude for planning and design.
As a front-end, I use vanilla-javascript for a project and I have decided to use vue.js as framework.

In addition to it, I would really love to talk to foreigners so I have been studying English for 30 minutes a day.
skills: Experience in building front-end with React, Redux, Vue.js, Vuex.
Experience in working with AWS cloud infrastructure development.
Experience in launching new products that require planning, design and development.
Experience in building back-end with Node.js, Java and PHP, and data store (RDBMS – MySQL, NoSQL – Redis)
Always thinking of improving efficiency of development teams.
